    # Multi Agent Workflow Rules

## Before Any Task

1. Read `.agents/workflow.md`
2. Identify the responsible agent
3. Follow that agent's instructions
4. Use existing artifacts as source of truth
5. Do NOT write code if PRD, Architecture, or Database is not yet available

## Agent Execution Order

```
Director
  → Analyst
  → Architect
  → Database
  → UI Designer
  → Developer
  → QA
```

## Conflict Resolution Hierarchy

| Priority | Rule |
|----------|------|
| 1 | PRD wins over implementation |
| 2 | Architecture wins over Developer |
| 3 | Database Architect wins over schema changes |
| 4 | QA must NOT modify requirements |

## Documentation

Always update related documentation when making changes.

## Artifact Source of Truth

| Artifact | Authority |
|----------|-----------|
| `docs/prd.md` | Product requirements |
| `docs/architecture.md` | System design |
| `database/schema.sql` | Database schema |
| `ui/design-system.md` | UI specifications |
| `docs/api-spec.md` | API contracts |
